This Cybersecurity Fundamentals course provides a comprehensive introduction to the evolving 
landscape of digital security. Beginning with the historical evolution of security practices, 
the course delves into the core concepts of cybersecurity, including its importance, common threats,
 and risk assessment methodologies. Participants will explore key security domains and principles, 
 learn about various security frameworks and controls, and gain hands-on experience with cybersecurity
 tools and techniques, including basic Python scripting. The course concludes with a focus on network 
 security, covering network components, architecture, security hardening principles, incident 
 response, and vulnerability analysis. By the end of this course, participants will have a 
 foundational understanding of cybersecurity concepts and practical skills to address the 
 challenges of securing digital assets in today's interconnected world.